<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 6:50PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Catoosa, northwestern
Whitfield and central Walker Counties through 715 PM EDT...
At 649 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms extended from Apison
to Rock Spring. These storms were drifting southeast at 5 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Ringgold, Fort Oglethorpe, Varnell, Tunnel Hill, Cohutta, Noble, Wood
Station, Indian Springs, Graysville, Blue Spring, Boynton, Beaumont
and Rock Spring.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
